list.abstract: contest是一种国外盛行的网络工作模式，通过Contest 竞赛方式，雇主可以从多个作品中选择最佳作品。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, new contest. What are you doing?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好，来场新的比赛。你要干什么？

yingyinNormal.en: Chandler, relax, it's not a contest. Certainly not a close one.
yingyinNormal.zh: 钱德，轻松一点，这不是比赛，不是实力相近的比赛。

yingyinNormal.en: What contest? Oh, it's something we started in the old neighborhood.
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么比赛？这是我们在之前的社区组织的比赛。

yingyinNormal.en: As you've heard this morning, I was in a Miss Fire Prevention Contest.
yingyinNormal.zh: 各位在今天早上已经听说了，我参加了防火小姐比赛。

yingyinNormal.en: Come on. We're trying to win a contest here. Forget it. I'm not wearing the wig.
yingyinNormal.zh: 拜托，我们可是要去比赛争冠军。想也别想，反正我不戴假发。

yingyinNormal.en: Pie eating contest? You assume because I was heavy that's the only way I could win something?
yingyinNormal.zh: 吃派大赛呢？因为我很胖，你就以为那是我唯一能赢的比赛吗？

yingyinNormal.en: This contest is war. This stage is the battlefield. Your song is your weapon.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这次比赛就好比一场战争，这个舞台就是你们的战场，你们的歌声就是你们的武器。

yingyinNormal.en: It's a contest for young unknown writers, and I might have, oh, my god, submitted you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是给没名气的年轻小说家的一次比赛，我也许已经…天哪...和你说过了。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh yeah, I hear you, girls. I mean, what am I doing here sitting worrying about some silly contest?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我明白，姑娘们，我是说，我干嘛坐在这为某个白痴比赛忧心忡忡？

yingyinNormal.en: When I was younger, I entered this pie eating contest. I ate so many that the thought of them makes me sick.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我小时候参加过一个吃派比赛，吃的太多了，导致我一想就恶心。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, it happens to everyone eventually. Come on, de la Cruzito, you've got a contest to win.
yingyinNormal.zh: 别愁眉不展的了，所有人都会走这一遭的，来吧，小德拉库斯，你还要去赢得比赛呢。

yingyinNormal.en: That's a wise policy. I once borrowed my sister's makeup for a costume contest. Got a terrible case of pinkeye.
yingyinNormal.zh: 十分明智的原则，我曾为化装比赛借用了我妹妹的化妆品，结果被传染到红眼病。

yingyinNormal.en: You are so lucky that I have to go to work today, or I would show you scary. I would win your little contest.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你真走运，我今天要去上班，否则我会让你见识一下什么叫吓人，我会赢得你的小比赛。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, heads up, we're doing crap-your-pants scary on account of the contest, so I just hope we don't offend you over here in candy land.
yingyinNormal.zh: 提醒一下，我们要举行吓出屎来的恐怖比赛，希望不会冒犯到糖果乐园的你们。

yingyinNormal.en: I asked you here for what comes after. What would Halliday say? James Halliday is dead. Yeah. He is. All that's left of him is this contest. And you know what? It just seems like he wouldn't want you winning it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我请你来是为了更长远的以后。哈利迪会怎么看？詹姆斯·哈利迪已经死了。没错，他死了。他留下的只有这场比赛。知道吗？他似乎不希望你赢得这场比赛。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay. Just for the record, I have never entered a wet T-shirt contest. I've won a few, but that's just because I spill when I'm drunk, So...
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，不过我得声明一下，我从来没参加过湿衣比赛，我赢过，但是因为我醉时喝酒洒了一身所以...

yingyinNormal.en: Halliday's contest is vitally important. I mean, it's nothing less than a war for control of the future. But this Parzival? He's not even clanned up. He's alone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哈利迪的比赛至关重要。这不亚于一场争夺未来控制权的战争。这个帕西法尔甚至都没有组队。他单打独斗。

yingyinNormal.en: We have an army. And yet, he's got the first key. Yeah, he has a key, but you have to get three of them to win the contest. Our stock dove 6% yesterday.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们有一支军队。但第一把钥匙给他找到了。没错，他是有了一把钥匙，但你得拥有三把才能赢得比赛。昨天我们的股价跌了六个点。

yingyinNormal.en: Maybe it's a contest. You know, like collect all five.
yingyinNormal.zh: 或者这是一场竞赛, 比如集满五个有奖？

yingyinNormal.en: All of this implies we win the contest. Indeed, it does.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这意味着我们必须得赢得挑战才行。没错，是的。
